    <bibl><title>L'Italia</title>,
<date when="1912-07-21">July 21, 1912</date>.
<title level="a">[ITALIAN COMPANY IN RECEIVERSHIP]</title></bibl>
   </div>
  </front>
  <body>
   <p>The Central Trust Company was appointed Receiver of the well-known Giacomo Allegretti Company, candy manufacturers, until a bankruptcy comptroller is chosen. Liabilities, twenty-five-thousand dollars ($25,000), while the firm has assets of only ten-thousand dollars ($10,000). Mr. Allegretti stated that the Candy Industry is in a critical period. The public cannot afford to buy candy, and when they do they economize on cheaper brands.</p>
